# Use Case Types

## Purpose
Each use case has a companion `*.types.ts` file that declares its input and
output contracts as TypeScript `type` aliases. These types are the boundary
between the delivery mechanism and the application layer ‚Äî controllers map
their DTOs into a `Command`, and the use case returns a `Result`. Using `type`
over `class` keeps these shapes as pure compile-time contracts with no runtime
overhead. Domain entities may appear in `Result` types because the application
layer is allowed to import from the domain layer.

> **Related rules:**
> - @use-case.mdc ‚Äî how Command and Result are consumed in execute()
> - @presentation/controller.mdc ‚Äî how DTOs are mapped into Commands

---

## Non-Negotiables

- Always use `type`, never `class` or `interface`
- Always suffix input type with `Command`, output type with `Result`
- Always co-locate in the same folder as the `*.usecase.ts` file
- When `execute` returns `void`, declare only the `Command` ‚Äî no `Result` type
- When a use case takes no input, use `UseCase<void, Result>` ‚Äî never declare an empty `Command = {}`
- Search commands must extend `OffsetPaginatedCommand` or `CursorPaginatedCommand` ‚Äî never declare `page` and `size` inline
- Never re-declare `Page<T>` ‚Äî import from `shared/domain/entities/page.entity.ts`

---

## Patterns

### ‚úÖ Correct ‚Äî mutation use case (Command + Result)

```typescript
import { Truck } from '../../../domain/entities/truck.entity';

export type CreateTruckCommand = {
  licensePlate: string;
  brand: string;
  model: string;
  year: number;
};

export type CreateTruckResult = {
  truck: Truck;
};
```

### ‚úÖ Correct ‚Äî void use case (Command only)

```typescript
export type DeleteTruckCommand = {
  id: number;
};
```

### ‚úÖ Correct ‚Äî no-input use case (void Command)

```typescript
import { Truck } from '../../../domain/entities/truck.entity';

export type FindAllTrucksResult = {
  trucks: Truck[];
};
```

```typescript
export class FindAllTrucksUseCase implements UseCase<void, FindAllTrucksResult> {
  async execute(): Promise<FindAllTrucksResult> { ... }
}
```

### ‚úÖ Correct ‚Äî search use case (paginated + filters + sort)

```typescript
import { OffsetPaginatedCommand } from '../../../../shared/application/usecases/paginated.command';

export type SearchTrucksCommand = OffsetPaginatedCommand & {
  filters: TruckFilters;
  sort: TruckSort;
};

export type SearchTrucksResult = {
  page: Page<Truck>;
};
```

### ‚ùå Wrong

```typescript
export class CreateTruckCommand { // use type, not class
  licensePlate: string;
}

export interface CreateTruckResult { // use type, not interface
  truck: Truck;
}

export type FindAllTrucksCommand = {}; // use void in UseCase<void, Result> instead
```

